commitResults.messageBody:
Let's ignore the validity of assessment types (Paths, Missions...),
i.e. an assessment can be named as "B01" although there exists no
assessment type that corresponds to the letter "B".

Checking for validity of assessment types is unavailable since
the AssessmentList class has yet been implemented.

commitResults.messageBody: Unresolved bug: already exist student in group not detected.

The command doesn't detect whether the specified student already
exists in the group since group doesn't keep track of its students.

Let's
* keep track of students in a group using a list of IDs
* modify implementation of add-alloc command accordingly so that it
doesn't allow adding duplicate students into one group
